-- Egypt Orders Detentions After Fatal Unrest Outside Cathedral
-- B y   A h m e d   E l - S a y e d   a n d   M a r i a m   F a m
-- 2013-04-13T14:56:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-13/egypt-orders-detentions-after-fatal-unrest-outside-cathedral.html
Prosecution orders the detention
for four days of 10 suspects, including four Christians, accused
of killing, attempted killing and causing damage to St. Mark’s
Coptic Orthodox Cathedral, according to a faxed prosecution
statement.
*Suspects denied accusations: statement
*Prosecution orders the arrest of 10 others: statement
*Note: Muslim-Christian fighting outside a Coptic cathedral in
Cairo and in a nearby town before that have left several people
killed this month.
*Note:  Egypt ’s Coptic pope criticized the handling of Islamist
President Mohamed Mursi of the violence.  To contact the reporter on this story:
